00:04:48,421 --> 00:04:53,492
? I saw you standing
in the shadows?

38
00:04:55,194 --> 00:05:01,333
? Watching over me
at night?

39
00:05:01,335 --> 00:05:06,405
? I'm gonna swim
across this ocean?

40
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:14,579
? But I can't do it
on my own?

41
00:05:14,581 --> 00:05:21,420
? I'm lost in
my weakness?

42
00:05:21,422 --> 00:05:27,359
? I'm breaking
into pieces?

43
00:05:30,096 --> 00:05:35,767
? Is anyone
waiting for me?

44
00:05:35,769 --> 00:05:41,573
? On the other side
of the street??

45
00:05:41,575 --> 00:05:49,648
? I need a lift
to take me home?

46
00:05:55,988 --> 00:06:02,594
? How do I keep
moving on?

47
00:06:02,596 --> 00:06:07,666
? If all that I love
is gone??

48
00:06:07,668 --> 00:06:15,741
? I need a sign
to give me hope?

49
00:06:58,251 --> 00:07:00,819
[Knocks loudly]

50
00:07:30,650 --> 00:07:32,884
can I help you?

51
00:07:34,921 --> 00:07:37,989
Are you, uh,
wallace russo?

52
00:07:37,991 --> 00:07:40,592
That would be mrs. Wallace
to you, young man. And you are?

53
00:07:40,594 --> 00:07:42,761
Your problem for
the next nine months.

54
00:07:42,763 --> 00:07:44,796
I will not be disrespected
in my own home.

55
00:07:44,798 --> 00:07:47,966
I don't care who you are
or what you want from me.

56
00:07:51,070 --> 00:07:53,472
I'm only gonna ask
your name one more time.

57
00:07:57,577 --> 00:08:00,479
You can stay out here
until you find out.

58
00:08:31,677 --> 00:08:33,512
[Knocking on door]

59
00:08:38,417 --> 00:08:40,986
[knocking louder]

60
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:50,595
my name is aldo russo.

61
00:08:50,597 --> 00:08:53,031
You do speak.
Well, come in.

62
00:09:04,143 --> 00:09:06,678
You're not what
I expected.

63
00:09:06,680 --> 00:09:08,480
Sorry to be
a disappointment.

64
00:09:08,482 --> 00:09:10,382
I didn't mean it
like that.

65
00:09:12,485 --> 00:09:14,452
Why don't you
go eat your food

66
00:09:14,454 --> 00:09:16,821
before it gets
any more cold
than it is.

67
00:09:16,823 --> 00:09:18,957
Can I just
go to bed?

68
00:09:18,959 --> 00:09:21,793
I thought there was
supposed to be
a social worker with you.

69
00:09:21,795 --> 00:09:25,430
I didn't expect you
to be alone.

70
00:09:25,432 --> 00:09:27,799
Well, I am.

71
00:09:27,801 --> 00:09:30,068
Your room
is upstairs.

72
00:10:22,121 --> 00:10:25,523
[Sobbing]

73
00:11:10,136 --> 00:11:12,971
[dialing]

74
00:11:25,651 --> 00:11:28,787
hi, you reached emilia.</l>
sorry i...</l>

75
00:11:28,789 --> 00:11:30,955
- mom!</l>
- aldo, I'm on the phone.</l>

76
00:11:30,957 --> 00:11:34,592
aldo!</l>
[laughing]

77
00:11:34,594 --> 00:11:36,227
[answering machine beeps]

78
00:11:36,229 --> 00:11:38,630
i, um...

79
00:11:43,502 --> 00:11:46,671
Stupid.
This is so stupid.

80
00:11:48,974 --> 00:11:51,810
I know
you won't get this.

81
00:11:54,680 --> 00:11:57,649
I just needed
to hear your voice.

82
00:11:57,651 --> 00:11:59,884
I just wanted to...

83
00:12:12,231 --> 00:12:14,332
[Dial tone droning]

84
00:12:14,334 --> 00:12:17,635
[dialing]

85
00:14:32,571 --> 00:14:34,639
you hungry?

86
00:14:37,142 --> 00:14:40,044
Well, if you
get hungry...

87
00:15:44,877 --> 00:15:46,711
Can I sit down?

88
00:15:46,713 --> 00:15:48,813
I was just getting up.

89
00:15:50,549 --> 00:15:52,984
Go ahead. Finish.

90
00:16:26,151 --> 00:16:28,720
Hi. I'm lorri mcglocklin.

91
00:16:28,722 --> 00:16:30,788
I'm aldo's
social worker.

92
00:16:30,790 --> 00:16:32,790
I am so sorry I'm late.
I fully intended to--

93
00:16:32,792 --> 00:16:35,560
- come in.
- Okay.

94
00:16:35,562 --> 00:16:38,496
You know, miss scott
from the d.H.S in jersey,

95
00:16:38,498 --> 00:16:41,399
she wasn't able to
forward me all of
the information

96
00:16:41,401 --> 00:16:43,668
in time for
aldo's arrival.

97
00:16:43,670 --> 00:16:46,437
Doesn't help that
we are so understaffed.

98
00:16:46,439 --> 00:16:48,172
- Please sit down.
- Oh, thank you.

99
00:16:48,174 --> 00:16:51,042
Hi. Well, at any rate,

100
00:16:51,044 --> 00:16:53,878
we're all
caught up now,

101
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:56,881
and I apologize
on our behalf.

102
00:16:56,883 --> 00:17:00,885
We'll work together
to make this a smooth
transition, okay?

103
00:17:09,661 --> 00:17:12,897
Well, uh, why don't
we start with you.

104
00:17:12,899 --> 00:17:16,401
- How did it happen?
- I'm sorry?

105
00:17:16,403 --> 00:17:19,470
- The accident.
- That information
wasn't released to you?

106
00:17:19,472 --> 00:17:22,740
I didn't get
all the details.

107
00:17:22,742 --> 00:17:25,209
You know what? Mrs. Wallace,
if you don't mind,

108
00:17:25,211 --> 00:17:28,079
- we can start
someplace else--
- why do you care?!

109
00:17:28,081 --> 00:17:30,281
I am trying to understand.

110
00:17:30,283 --> 00:17:31,983
It doesn't matter!

111
00:17:31,985 --> 00:17:34,285
I'm here and she's dead!

112
00:17:34,287 --> 00:17:38,556
- She's dead!
- I just wanna
understand what happened.

113
00:17:42,061 --> 00:17:44,128
Look...

114
00:17:44,130 --> 00:17:46,631
Mrs. Wallace,

115
00:17:46,633 --> 00:17:50,935
it's very important that
this is something you wanna do,

116
00:17:50,937 --> 00:17:54,872
in order to make
this relationship work.

117
00:17:54,874 --> 00:17:57,208
Well, at the end of the day,

118
00:17:57,210 --> 00:17:59,310
I don't really think I have
anything to offer him.

119
00:17:59,312 --> 00:18:01,913
You do, you do.
You can offer
him comfort.

120
00:18:01,915 --> 00:18:04,916
Comfort's a pretty hard
thing to come by

121
00:18:04,918 --> 00:18:07,819
for a kid in
his position.

122
00:18:07,821 --> 00:18:10,154
Don't you think so?

123
00:18:10,156 --> 00:18:12,790
It's not about
what I think or what I feel.

124
00:18:12,792 --> 00:18:16,127
Emilia is still dead.
He will never let that go.

125
00:18:17,796 --> 00:18:20,031
Does he remind you
of emilia?

126
00:18:26,038 --> 00:18:28,539
Yes. Sometimes.

127
00:18:28,541 --> 00:18:31,843
I've made good
by not letting him know.

128
00:18:45,724 --> 00:18:48,092
My past has been
very confusing.

129
00:18:48,094 --> 00:18:50,461
I've done a lot of things
I'm not proud of

130
00:18:50,463 --> 00:18:54,799
that I wish I could've
done differently.

131
00:18:58,804 --> 00:19:01,539
Listen, mrs. Wallace,

132
00:19:01,541 --> 00:19:04,876
whatever happened
in your past,

133
00:19:04,878 --> 00:19:07,211
it just doesn't matter,

134
00:19:07,213 --> 00:19:09,881
because I think there
might be something
good in there

135
00:19:09,883 --> 00:19:12,984
for both of you.

136
00:19:12,986 --> 00:19:16,554
Why don't you let me
go through this whole
program with you.

137
00:19:16,556 --> 00:19:19,223
Okay? I'm gonna take you
through it step by step,

138
00:19:19,225 --> 00:19:21,259
and I'm gonna give you
all the information,

139
00:19:21,261 --> 00:19:24,896
and we'll talk
about your options.

140
00:19:24,898 --> 00:19:26,664
Is that okay?

141
00:19:31,870 --> 00:19:34,105
Yeah.

142
00:19:35,541 --> 00:19:37,475
Okay.

143
00:19:44,716 --> 00:19:49,020
[Water running]

144
00:21:16,408 --> 00:21:18,809
[knocking on door]

145
00:21:22,981 --> 00:21:25,016
[knocking continues]

146
00:21:34,293 --> 00:21:36,560
[knocking louder]

147
00:21:39,698 --> 00:21:42,033
oh, uh...

148
00:21:42,035 --> 00:21:44,769
[Giggles]
sorry.

149
00:21:44,771 --> 00:21:47,204
- Hi.
- Hi.

150
00:21:47,206 --> 00:21:49,974
Um, is mrs. Wallace here?

151
00:21:52,110 --> 00:21:56,347
I don't know.
You can look around
if you want.

152
00:22:04,990 --> 00:22:06,957
I've never
seen you before.

153
00:22:09,294 --> 00:22:12,963
- You live here now?
- Just passing through.

154
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:16,767
Temporary.

155
00:22:16,769 --> 00:22:19,770
Well... I'm sure
you'll find it

156
00:22:19,772 --> 00:22:22,273
very warm at
mrs. Wallace's.

157
00:22:25,544 --> 00:22:27,445
What's your relation?

158
00:22:27,447 --> 00:22:30,381
Still trying to
figure that out.

159
00:22:31,817 --> 00:22:34,151
Not much of
a conversationalist, are you?

160
00:22:34,153 --> 00:22:36,487
Not much conversation
to be had.

161
00:22:40,659 --> 00:22:44,195
- Well...
I'm gonna go.
- Yeah.

162
00:22:46,031 --> 00:22:48,299
I come here on saturdays

163
00:22:48,301 --> 00:22:50,735
to help mrs. Wallace
out around the house,

164
00:22:50,737 --> 00:22:52,803
but since she's not here,

165
00:22:52,805 --> 00:22:55,406
can you tell her that
madalyn stopped by?

166
00:22:55,408 --> 00:22:59,110
- Sure.
- Thanks.

167
00:24:36,908 --> 00:24:38,375
Perfect.

168
00:24:46,785 --> 00:24:49,687
[Engine sputters]

169
00:26:38,530 --> 00:26:41,365
- what are you doing?
- I didn't mean to--

170
00:26:41,367 --> 00:26:44,034
to what, touch things
you're not supposed to
be touching in the first place?

171
00:26:44,036 --> 00:26:46,637
- I didn't think
that you'd mind.
- Well, I do mind,

172
00:26:46,639 --> 00:26:49,273
and why is
no concern of yours.

173
00:27:34,119 --> 00:27:37,655
[Sound of brakes screeching,
metal colliding]

174
00:27:41,059 --> 00:27:44,294
[sobbing]

175
00:29:08,880 --> 00:29:10,948
[container clatters
on floor]

176
00:29:39,210 --> 00:29:41,245
- hi, mrs. Wallace.
- Hey.

177
00:29:41,247 --> 00:29:44,181
- Nice day, isn't it?
- Mm-hmm.

178
00:29:44,183 --> 00:29:46,350
Let me help you
with this.

179
00:29:46,352 --> 00:29:48,619
Thank you, sweetheart.
You never came by
last week.

180
00:29:48,621 --> 00:29:50,854
Something special happen?

181
00:29:50,856 --> 00:29:53,223
I did, but
you weren't home.

182
00:29:53,225 --> 00:29:56,026
I left a message
with that boy
who's staying here.

183
00:29:56,028 --> 00:30:00,097
- Oh, well,
he never talks much.
- Yeah, I got that impression.

184
00:30:00,099 --> 00:30:02,699
I'm sure there's
some good in him.

185
00:30:02,701 --> 00:30:04,601
It's just getting
it out that's hard.

186
00:30:04,603 --> 00:30:07,871
- What's his name?
- Aldo. He's my grandson.

187
00:30:07,873 --> 00:30:11,708
Mrs. Wallace,
you never told me
you had a grandson.

188
00:30:11,710 --> 00:30:14,011
I didn't know
I had one.

189
00:30:14,013 --> 00:30:16,513
Is emilia all right?

190
00:30:20,418 --> 00:30:23,453
- She died.
- Oh, my god.

191
00:30:24,522 --> 00:30:27,558
Mrs. Wallace,
I am so sorry.

192
00:30:27,560 --> 00:30:30,360
- I shouldn't even
be prying into--
- oh, honey.

193
00:30:30,362 --> 00:30:33,163
You know
there's no secrets here.

194
00:31:10,535 --> 00:31:13,604
Maybe see if
he'll come help us.

195
00:31:15,840 --> 00:31:18,375
You sure?

196
00:31:18,377 --> 00:31:20,544
It doesn't seem like
he wants to be bothered.

197
00:31:20,546 --> 00:31:23,413
That's his natural look.
Go on.

198
00:31:39,030 --> 00:31:41,265
We never formally met.

199
00:31:41,267 --> 00:31:43,834
I'm madalyn.

200
00:31:52,010 --> 00:31:54,745
Wanna come down here
and give us a hand?

201
00:31:56,080 --> 00:32:00,517
We could really use
the extra pair of hands.

202
00:32:00,519 --> 00:32:03,620
I promise you it's not
as girly as you might think.

203
00:32:27,845 --> 00:32:30,514
So what are you
writing about?

204
00:32:35,887 --> 00:32:38,722
You're persistent.

205
00:32:38,724 --> 00:32:41,358
You look like
you can use a friend.

206
00:32:41,360 --> 00:32:43,527
A matter of opinion.

207
00:32:43,529 --> 00:32:46,797
An opinion I'm sure
I didn't really ask you for.

208
00:32:46,799 --> 00:32:49,666
I just thought,
since you're new
in town and all...

209
00:32:51,836 --> 00:32:55,505
Do us both a favor.
Go back to gardening, okay?

210
00:32:55,507 --> 00:32:58,608
Go ahead.
Run along. Shoo.

211
00:33:05,183 --> 00:33:07,751
I'm sorry for your loss.

212
00:33:10,688 --> 00:33:14,024
Could you please
just leave?

213
00:33:15,360 --> 00:33:17,594
I'm sorry. I didn't
mean to...

214
00:33:17,596 --> 00:33:21,631
Look, I don't know you,
and I don't wanna
fucking know you.

215
00:33:21,633 --> 00:33:23,834
- Hey, aldo.
- I'm sorry,
mrs. Wallace.

216
00:33:23,836 --> 00:33:25,535
I was just
trying to help.

217
00:33:25,537 --> 00:33:28,672
Will you both
just leave me alone?

218
00:33:28,674 --> 00:33:30,741
I'm gonna go,
mrs. Wallace.

219
00:33:30,743 --> 00:33:33,210
No, no, stay.
Don't let him
bother you.

220
00:33:33,212 --> 00:33:35,479
Come on.

221
00:34:12,750 --> 00:34:15,052
I brought you some food.
I know you must be hungry.

222
00:34:15,054 --> 00:34:17,654
You haven't been
downstairs all day.

223
00:34:19,123 --> 00:34:21,258
- I'll just leave it here.
- Don't bother.

224
00:34:21,260 --> 00:34:23,026
What did you say?

225
00:34:23,028 --> 00:34:25,929
I said don't bother!

226
00:34:25,931 --> 00:34:28,198
I'm not gonna
eat that.

227
00:34:28,200 --> 00:34:31,334
- And you can stop being
so fake while you're at it.
- How dare you?

228
00:34:31,336 --> 00:34:33,336
I've tried the best I can
to make this work.

229
00:34:33,338 --> 00:34:36,273
You are not gonna make me
seem like the bad guy here.

230
00:34:36,275 --> 00:34:39,176
You are the one with
the problem, not me.

231
00:34:39,178 --> 00:34:41,912
I'm sure that's what
my mother was to you, right?
Something to get over.

232
00:36:25,550 --> 00:36:27,284
Aldo.

233
00:36:30,454 --> 00:36:32,522
Aldo.

234
00:36:32,524 --> 00:36:34,524
Aldo!

235
00:36:37,728 --> 00:36:39,663
- Aldo.
- What do you--

236
00:36:39,665 --> 00:36:44,100
- what the fuck?!
You old bitch!
- It's gotta stop.

237
00:36:44,102 --> 00:36:46,503
What do you want from me?

238
00:36:46,505 --> 00:36:49,272
- You are not the only
one living here.
- I don't wanna live here.

239
00:36:49,274 --> 00:36:51,708
You can have your tantrums,
be all depressed if you want to.

240
00:36:51,710 --> 00:36:54,544
I refuse to be,
and I refuse to let you

241
00:36:54,546 --> 00:36:56,246
walk all over that place
like you don't care,
like no one cares.

242
00:36:56,248 --> 00:36:59,216
Listen, I'm only your problem
until next summer,

243
00:36:59,218 --> 00:37:01,851
so you won't have to
worry about it anymore.

244
00:37:01,853 --> 00:37:04,020
Until then, I'm gonna
get some respect from you.

245
00:37:04,022 --> 00:37:06,823
I don't have to
listen to this.
You're not my mother.

246
00:37:06,825 --> 00:37:08,525
Right. I'm not your mother.

247
00:37:08,527 --> 00:37:10,927
I do not deserve
to be treated like this.

248
00:37:10,929 --> 00:37:13,930
I know emilia raised you
better than that.

249
00:37:13,932 --> 00:37:15,699
- What did you say?
- You're gonna hit
an old woman?

250
00:37:15,701 --> 00:37:18,735
I dare you. I dare you!

251
00:37:19,837 --> 00:37:21,571
[Frustrated yell]

252
00:37:24,275 --> 00:37:27,244
- you don't know me.
- That's right,
I don't know you.

253
00:37:27,246 --> 00:37:29,713
I don't pretend
to know you.

254
00:37:29,715 --> 00:37:32,182
I don't consider you
a child, but you sure
are acting like one.

255
00:37:32,184 --> 00:37:34,784
Consider me gone.

256
00:37:34,786 --> 00:37:37,821
You're not going anywhere.
Get back in the house.
You have school tomorrow, aldo.

257
00:37:38,723 --> 00:37:42,559
Aldo! Aldo!

258
00:37:42,561 --> 00:37:46,463
Aldo!

259
00:38:06,917 --> 00:38:10,186
Well, lord, where have
you been hidin'?

260
00:38:10,188 --> 00:38:12,589
Hiding. Wish I could.

261
00:38:12,591 --> 00:38:14,824
Madalyn came by.

262
00:38:14,826 --> 00:38:17,327
She told you?

263
00:38:17,329 --> 00:38:20,096
Oh, shirley, I don't
know what I'm doing.
I'm too old for this.

264
00:38:20,098 --> 00:38:22,899
Oh, wallace, you just old
when it's convenient for you.

265
00:38:26,370 --> 00:38:28,505
So...

266
00:38:28,507 --> 00:38:30,407
He's your daughter's son.

267
00:38:30,409 --> 00:38:33,743
Shirley, he's so beautiful.
He looks just like her.

268
00:38:33,745 --> 00:38:36,212
Well, I believe it.
The sun envied that girl.

269
00:38:36,214 --> 00:38:39,349
- He is so angry.
- As well he should be.

270
00:38:39,351 --> 00:38:42,552
And he's disrespectful,
and he's rude, not to
mention, his name is aldo.

271
00:38:42,554 --> 00:38:45,088
Oh, he's an aldo junior.

272
00:38:45,090 --> 00:38:48,692
He doesn't even know
his grandfather's name
was aldo.

273
00:38:48,694 --> 00:38:52,362
Every time I look at him,
I see emilia and aldo.

274
00:38:52,364 --> 00:38:55,765
He looks more like her,
but he's hard-headed like
the old man was.

275
00:38:55,767 --> 00:38:58,068
Well, he's probably
in pain, hurt.

276
00:38:58,070 --> 00:39:00,603
He's just young
and needs somebody
to guide him.

277
00:39:00,605 --> 00:39:03,173
Plus, he's livin'
with a stranger.

278
00:39:03,175 --> 00:39:05,775
Stranger?! Stranger?

279
00:39:05,777 --> 00:39:09,179
- Is that what I am?
- That's exactly what you
are, wallace, a stranger.

280
00:39:09,181 --> 00:39:12,182
That boy doesn't know you.
He's never even met you.

281
00:39:12,184 --> 00:39:13,717
What did you
expect him to do,

282
00:39:13,719 --> 00:39:16,086
just come in and instantly
run into your arms?

283
00:39:16,088 --> 00:39:18,822
- Well?
- You know you ran
your daughter off.

284
00:39:18,824 --> 00:39:20,890
How many times you
gonna tell me that?

285
00:39:20,892 --> 00:39:23,159
- Until you get it
through your head.
- Well, it is through.

286
00:39:23,161 --> 00:39:25,729
In one ear
and right out the other.

287
00:39:25,731 --> 00:39:28,765
What happened between
you and her is what
put that man in his grave.

288
00:39:28,767 --> 00:39:31,735
I'll never understand it.
That girl dreamt of
being anywhere but here.

289
00:39:31,737 --> 00:39:34,037
She never cared about
nobody but herself.

290
00:39:34,039 --> 00:39:36,606
Wallace, how can you
go and say somethin'
like that?

291
00:39:36,608 --> 00:39:39,109
Care. Care!
She loved you, wallace.

292
00:39:39,111 --> 00:39:41,211
She wanted more
for her life.

293
00:39:41,213 --> 00:39:43,713
She wanted more
for her life than
just livin' in a house

294
00:39:43,715 --> 00:39:47,016
that's been here
hundreds of years,
and I don't blame her.

295
00:39:47,018 --> 00:39:49,819
That girl wanted
to see the world.

296
00:39:49,821 --> 00:39:51,921
And I remember.

297
00:39:51,923 --> 00:39:54,391
She waited, and she
waited for your approval.

298
00:39:54,393 --> 00:39:56,826
You never gave it to her,
so what did she do?

299
00:39:56,828 --> 00:40:00,163
She left,
and when she did,

300
00:40:00,165 --> 00:40:02,565
aldo was never the same.

301
00:40:02,567 --> 00:40:05,535
Mm-mm. He was not
right after that.

302
00:40:05,537 --> 00:40:08,071
Now listen to me, sister.

303
00:40:09,340 --> 00:40:13,243
You get a second chance
now with this boy.

304
00:40:13,245 --> 00:40:15,545
Most people don't
get a second chance, wallace,

305
00:40:15,547 --> 00:40:18,047
but god gave that to you.

306
00:40:18,049 --> 00:40:20,550
Don't you run this boy off
like you did her.

307
00:40:20,552 --> 00:40:23,119
You hear me?

308
00:40:24,488 --> 00:40:27,390
Now come on.
Let's go get us some tea.

309
00:41:28,319 --> 00:41:31,421
[Knocking on door]
time for school.

310
00:41:31,423 --> 00:41:33,590
Get up.

311
00:41:33,592 --> 00:41:37,560
- I'm not going.
- That's what you think.

312
00:41:51,108 --> 00:41:53,343
What the hell?!

313
00:41:53,345 --> 00:41:55,712
- Time for school.
- Are you crazy?

314
00:41:55,714 --> 00:41:57,714
Get dressed.
The bus is coming
in an hour.

315
00:41:57,716 --> 00:41:59,816
And I'm sure
I won't be there.

316
00:41:59,818 --> 00:42:01,851
And I'm sure
you will. Ha ha!

317
00:42:01,853 --> 00:42:05,488
[Angry yell]
oh, god!

318
00:42:43,527 --> 00:42:46,329
- Aldo.
- I went to
school, okay?

319
00:42:46,331 --> 00:42:48,998
- How was it?
- School.

320
00:42:49,000 --> 00:42:51,401
I know, but did
you meet anyone?

321
00:42:51,403 --> 00:42:53,603
Really, come on,
let's not do
this right now.

322
00:42:53,605 --> 00:42:55,872
- I'm gonna go to my room
if that's okay with you.
- Aldo, i--

323
00:42:55,874 --> 00:42:58,107
look, I'll go to
school and back
because you're forcing me.

324
00:42:58,109 --> 00:43:00,310
We don't have to
talk about it.

325
00:43:00,312 --> 00:43:03,413
We don't have to be
friends or anything,
okay?

326
00:43:03,415 --> 00:43:05,682
- Okay?
- [Thunder rumbling]

327
00:43:05,684 --> 00:43:09,552
so you just
leave me alone,
I'll leave you alone.

328
00:43:09,554 --> 00:43:12,388
It'll be like
I was never here.

329
00:43:36,013 --> 00:43:41,551
? I'm so tired
of the myth that goes?

330
00:43:41,553 --> 00:43:48,157
? That nice guys come first
and bad ones come last?

331
00:43:48,159 --> 00:43:51,227
? I should know by now

332
00:43:51,229 --> 00:43:54,097
? Things are not
what they seem?

333
00:43:54,099 --> 00:44:00,169
? And if I do,
then I must be crazy?

334
00:44:00,171 --> 00:44:05,808
? 'Cause time has taught me
that in order to play the game?

335
00:44:05,810 --> 00:44:13,149
? You must be willing to
throw away your self?

336
00:44:13,151 --> 00:44:17,387
? If I can't be
part of the game?

337
00:44:17,389 --> 00:44:25,461
? I'll end up losing
every ounce I have left?

338
00:44:25,763 --> 00:44:33,836
?

339
00:45:15,646 --> 00:45:18,448
[Phone rings]

340
00:45:23,487 --> 00:45:27,256
- [ringing continues]
- hello.

341
00:45:27,258 --> 00:45:31,461
Yes.
What are you saying?

342
00:46:33,056 --> 00:46:34,657
I thought being
waited up for

343
00:46:34,659 --> 00:46:37,160
- stopped when you were
12 years old.
- Stop it!

344
00:46:37,162 --> 00:46:40,329
Just stop. I've let you
walk all over me
these past months.

345
00:46:40,331 --> 00:46:43,132
I'm not gonna let you
stand there and lie
to my face.

346
00:46:43,134 --> 00:46:44,801
[Derisive laugh]
lie about what?

347
00:46:44,803 --> 00:46:46,702
You know what
I'm talking about.

348
00:46:46,704 --> 00:46:49,138
Your principal
called this morning.
You haven't been in school.

349
00:46:49,140 --> 00:46:51,474
I'm sitting there on the phone
feeling like a fool,

350
00:46:51,476 --> 00:46:52,809
feeling like
a goddamn fool,

351
00:46:52,811 --> 00:46:54,977
because it never
occurred to me

352
00:46:54,979 --> 00:46:58,047
that you could be
so deceptive, so manipulative.

353
00:46:58,049 --> 00:47:01,317
Aldo, I'm at a loss
for words.

354
00:47:01,319 --> 00:47:03,152
There's nothing
left to say.

355
00:47:03,154 --> 00:47:05,588
You can't stay here.
This just isn't gonna work.

356
00:47:05,590 --> 00:47:08,057
Pack your things and leave.
You're in god's hands now.

357
00:47:08,059 --> 00:47:10,560
Now you wanna bring
god into this.

358
00:47:10,562 --> 00:47:13,663
When he's ready,
I'll be here waiting.

359
00:47:13,665 --> 00:47:16,899
I'm sure he's already
figured out...

360
00:47:20,804 --> 00:47:23,139
Aldo. Aldo, stop.

361
00:47:23,141 --> 00:47:25,308
Who are you
trying to fool?

362
00:47:25,310 --> 00:47:28,811
Look around. There's
no one here for you
to be tough in front of.

363
00:47:28,813 --> 00:47:31,514
If you're in pain,
be in pain.

364
00:47:31,516 --> 00:47:33,883
If you're in mourning,
mourn. Why don't you cry?

365
00:47:33,885 --> 00:47:36,886
I am in pain!
I am angry!

366
00:47:36,888 --> 00:47:40,656
I've lost all feeling!

367
00:47:40,658 --> 00:47:45,728
I'm numb to everything.
Numb to everyone.

368
00:47:45,730 --> 00:47:48,631
Can't you see
that I'm suffering?

369
00:47:48,633 --> 00:47:51,133
[Crying]

370
00:47:51,135 --> 00:47:53,236
I'm not this person.

371
00:47:53,238 --> 00:47:56,873
I don't know
how I got like this.

372
00:47:56,875 --> 00:47:59,709
My life, it's so...

373
00:47:59,711 --> 00:48:01,878
I just want it to end.

374
00:48:03,547 --> 00:48:07,717
Aldo, stop.

375
00:48:10,020 --> 00:48:13,022
Do you know what it's like
to sit at home

376
00:48:13,024 --> 00:48:17,326
and wait for someone
who you know is never,
ever gonna come back?

377
00:48:19,529 --> 00:48:23,199
Still, you sit there
and you wait.

378
00:48:25,135 --> 00:48:27,203
You think to yourself,

379
00:48:27,205 --> 00:48:30,806
what was the last thing
I said to 'em?

380
00:48:30,808 --> 00:48:34,543
Did I say anything at all?
Do you know what that's like?

381
00:48:46,723 --> 00:48:49,492
I do.

382
00:48:49,494 --> 00:48:51,928
- Yeah.
- I do.

383
00:48:53,463 --> 00:48:56,799
I drove your mother away
and sat by that door for months,

384
00:48:56,801 --> 00:48:59,402
waiting for her
to walk through it.

385
00:48:59,404 --> 00:49:03,139
Waited by the phone
for a phone call.

386
00:49:03,141 --> 00:49:05,875
Mail couldn't get here
fast enough.

387
00:49:05,877 --> 00:49:08,110
Anything so I'd know
she was fine.

388
00:49:10,047 --> 00:49:12,982
It's my fault that
I wasn't in your life.

389
00:49:12,984 --> 00:49:15,584
It's my fault that
I don't know you.

390
00:49:17,988 --> 00:49:19,889
I wake up with that
every morning.

391
00:49:19,891 --> 00:49:27,129
I wake up with that
sense of lost time every day.

392
00:49:27,131 --> 00:49:30,800
But I refused to let it
do to me what it did before,

393
00:49:30,802 --> 00:49:34,804
what it did to
your grandfather,
what it did to us.

394
00:49:34,806 --> 00:49:37,073
[Sighs]

395
00:49:37,075 --> 00:49:39,642
I know what
you're going through.

396
00:49:39,644 --> 00:49:43,579
[Rueful chuckle]
believe me.

397
00:49:43,581 --> 00:49:45,648
I know very well.

398
00:49:48,852 --> 00:49:51,420
Emilia was taken from you.

399
00:49:53,156 --> 00:49:55,791
You had no choice.

400
00:49:55,793 --> 00:49:57,793
I had every choice.

401
00:49:57,795 --> 00:50:01,464
And I made the wrong choice.

402
00:50:01,466 --> 00:50:03,966
I'll never forgive
myself for that.

403
00:50:03,968 --> 00:50:07,236
I live with that
every day.

404
00:50:07,238 --> 00:50:11,040
I'll live with that
till the day I die.

405
00:50:26,490 --> 00:50:29,158
I'd like to stay...

406
00:50:29,160 --> 00:50:31,994
If you'd let me.

407
00:50:31,996 --> 00:50:34,296
I'm sorry.

408
00:50:34,298 --> 00:50:37,666
You didn't do
anything wrong.

409
00:50:37,668 --> 00:50:41,137
Look at the way I've been,
the way I've treated you.

410
00:50:41,139 --> 00:50:44,273
- I've been such an ass.
- How could you have known?

411
00:51:32,289 --> 00:51:34,490
I was wondering if
you wouldn't mind

412
00:51:34,492 --> 00:51:38,127
me taking a look
in the shed at the car.

413
00:51:38,129 --> 00:51:40,362
I know you don't like
people messin' with it and--

414
00:51:40,364 --> 00:51:44,633
go ahead. Nothing you can do
to it that hasn't already
been done.

415
00:51:44,635 --> 00:51:47,136
- Really?
- Sure.

416
00:52:07,023 --> 00:52:09,024
Madalyn: aldo?

417
00:52:13,563 --> 00:52:16,632
Mrs. Wallace told me
you'd be in here.

418
00:52:16,634 --> 00:52:18,868
Said you might
be thirsty.

419
00:52:22,172 --> 00:52:24,607
Peace offering?

420
00:52:29,913 --> 00:52:32,047
Is that freshly squeezed?

421
00:52:33,884 --> 00:52:35,885
I don't think so.

422
00:52:52,135 --> 00:52:55,738
Well, then,
the war must go on.

423
00:53:09,119 --> 00:53:12,221
This car's been
broken for a while.

424
00:53:15,992 --> 00:53:18,594
Not broken.

425
00:53:20,230 --> 00:53:22,464
Sleeping.

426
00:53:22,466 --> 00:53:26,702
So you're trying
to wake it up or something?

427
00:53:33,977 --> 00:53:37,813
- Trying.
- Maybe it wants to sleep.

428
00:53:43,053 --> 00:53:46,589
If you never try,
you'll never know.

429
00:54:02,906 --> 00:54:05,140
Can I help?

430
00:54:05,142 --> 00:54:09,078
Are you a girl
that likes to get dirty?

431
00:54:10,080 --> 00:54:12,381
Excuse me?

432
00:54:27,364 --> 00:54:29,531
Gloves.

433
00:54:56,293 --> 00:54:59,395
So I haven't
seen you at
school yet.

434
00:55:01,898 --> 00:55:05,634
- Yeah, I haven't
been going.
- Why?

435
00:55:05,636 --> 00:55:09,471
I guess I wasn't
quite ready for
the world yet.

436
00:55:09,473 --> 00:55:12,308
Is everything okay?

437
00:55:16,379 --> 00:55:18,681
I don't know.

438
00:55:44,674 --> 00:55:47,176
Like that car out there?

439
00:55:47,178 --> 00:55:50,112
Yeah, it's pretty cool.

440
00:55:50,114 --> 00:55:52,948
Where'd you learn
how to fix cars?

441
00:55:52,950 --> 00:55:55,851
My mom's car would break down
all the time,

442
00:55:55,853 --> 00:55:58,187
and she didn't have money
to pay someone to fix it,

443
00:55:58,189 --> 00:56:01,090
so someone had
to learn how to.

444
00:56:05,128 --> 00:56:06,662
What?

445
00:56:06,664 --> 00:56:09,665
Can I show you something?

446
00:56:09,667 --> 00:56:11,734
What?

447
00:56:26,516 --> 00:56:29,118
Look at this.

448
00:56:29,120 --> 00:56:31,453
Who's this?

449
00:56:31,455 --> 00:56:33,889
- Hey, that's the car.
- That's your grandfather.

450
00:56:40,130 --> 00:56:41,897
He looks just like me.

451
00:56:41,899 --> 00:56:46,368
I think it's you
that looks just like him.

452
00:56:51,341 --> 00:56:53,375
I'm named after him.

453
00:56:56,479 --> 00:56:58,313
I never knew that.

454
00:56:58,315 --> 00:57:00,783
There's a lot you and i
don't know about each other.

455
00:57:00,785 --> 00:57:03,619
Your grandfather
loved that car.

456
00:57:03,621 --> 00:57:06,455
I think that's why
you love it.

457
00:57:06,457 --> 00:57:08,624
I want you
to have it.

458
00:57:08,626 --> 00:57:11,260
- The picture?
- The car.

459
00:57:12,662 --> 00:57:14,396
- Really?
- On one condition.

460
00:57:14,398 --> 00:57:18,734
That you go back to school
and catch up on your studies.

461
00:57:19,903 --> 00:57:21,703
Okay.

462
00:57:24,274 --> 00:57:26,708
Can I keep this, too?

463
00:57:26,710 --> 00:57:28,710
Sure.

464
00:57:33,149 --> 00:57:35,684
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

465
00:57:40,290 --> 00:57:42,591
I'm gonna try
to be better.

466
00:57:51,468 --> 00:57:53,869
I wanna be better.

467
00:57:55,405 --> 00:57:57,973
I know.

468
00:59:05,975 --> 00:59:12,281
?

469
00:59:24,894 --> 00:59:31,366
?

470
00:59:43,479 --> 00:59:50,185
?

471
01:00:06,436 --> 01:00:13,108
?

472
01:00:17,647 --> 01:00:20,215
So things gettin'
better now?

473
01:00:20,217 --> 01:00:22,351
Well, I'm glad that
it happened,

474
01:00:22,353 --> 01:00:24,486
but now that
it has happened,

475
01:00:24,488 --> 01:00:26,521
sometimes I feel
more hopeless than
when it hadn't.

476
01:00:26,523 --> 01:00:28,824
Am I really all he needs,
is he what I need?

477
01:00:28,826 --> 01:00:31,560
You know, you've been
so set in your ways,
livin' your life,

478
01:00:31,562 --> 01:00:34,062
this boy comes along,
you don't know what to do.

479
01:00:34,064 --> 01:00:36,264
I want it to be
better for him.

480
01:00:36,266 --> 01:00:38,800
I see him starting
to be better, it makes
me wanna be better.

481
01:00:38,802 --> 01:00:41,637
I haven't felt
so alive in years.

482
01:00:41,639 --> 01:00:43,538
I just can't help
but wonder where
it's going from here.

483
01:00:43,540 --> 01:00:46,441
So hard to live
in the moment.

484
01:00:46,443 --> 01:00:48,777
- Is it too late?
- For what?

485
01:00:48,779 --> 01:00:50,779
As long as you got
life in you.

486
01:00:50,781 --> 01:00:53,281
- I've made so many mistakes.
- No, now, wallace,

487
01:00:53,283 --> 01:00:56,284
you made one big mistake,
and you've let it run
your life ever since.

488
01:00:56,286 --> 01:00:59,121
I was so wrong
about emilia,

489
01:00:59,123 --> 01:01:00,856
but I loved her so much,
I couldn't let her go.

490
01:01:00,858 --> 01:01:03,458
But there's nothing
wrong with that, honey.

491
01:01:03,460 --> 01:01:06,294
Oh, shirley, I wish
I could believe you.

492
01:01:06,296 --> 01:01:08,430
You know what?

493
01:01:08,432 --> 01:01:11,266
That boy's gonna change you
in ways you don't even know.

494
01:01:11,268 --> 01:01:13,502
I think he
already has.

495
01:01:17,040 --> 01:01:20,175
Can I tell you something?

496
01:01:20,177 --> 01:01:24,012
You deserve
to be happy.

497
01:01:24,014 --> 01:01:28,216
Wallace, it has just broken
my heart to watch what
you've put yourself through.

498
01:01:28,218 --> 01:01:31,553
But now, I know
what it was for.

499
01:01:31,555 --> 01:01:34,356
It was for this moment
right here.

500
01:01:36,125 --> 01:01:39,394
This moment right here.

501
01:01:41,130 --> 01:01:42,698
Thank you.

502
01:01:46,436 --> 01:01:48,670
[Shirley laughing]

503
01:02:04,954 --> 01:02:06,955
oh, I'm sorry.

504
01:02:06,957 --> 01:02:10,025
I didn't know
you were here.

505
01:02:10,027 --> 01:02:13,261
Um, I shouldn't have...
I shouldn't have done
anything.

506
01:02:13,263 --> 01:02:15,363
I'm really sorry.

507
01:02:16,799 --> 01:02:20,001
Could you do
something for me?

508
01:02:20,003 --> 01:02:21,937
- What?
- Come here.

509
01:02:23,473 --> 01:02:25,240
Okay.

510
01:02:27,610 --> 01:02:30,445
Could you tell me
about her?

511
01:02:30,447 --> 01:02:33,215
- About mom?
- Yeah.

512
01:02:33,217 --> 01:02:35,283
What was she like?

513
01:02:40,690 --> 01:02:43,024
I don't know...

514
01:02:43,026 --> 01:02:45,460
She used to always dream
about going to new york

515
01:02:45,462 --> 01:02:47,763
and seeing
the statue of liberty.

516
01:02:47,765 --> 01:02:49,765
Please do not remind me
of that trip.

517
01:02:49,767 --> 01:02:52,434
- She went?
- Yeah, we both went.

518
01:02:52,436 --> 01:02:55,771
We stayed at her friend's
studio for a week.

519
01:02:55,773 --> 01:03:00,542
All four of us...
It wasn't the best
of experiences.

520
01:03:00,544 --> 01:03:03,879
But me and mom
were really close.

521
01:03:03,881 --> 01:03:06,114
We told each other
everything.

522
01:03:06,116 --> 01:03:08,049
She was one of
my best friends.

523
01:03:08,051 --> 01:03:11,887
My only best friend;
we moved around a lot.

524
01:03:11,889 --> 01:03:15,757
I even tried to set her up
with a few of my friends'
single dads.

525
01:03:15,759 --> 01:03:19,027
She started dating
one of them, and I realized

526
01:03:19,029 --> 01:03:21,229
it wasn't
such a good idea.

527
01:03:25,201 --> 01:03:27,369
Let me show you something.

528
01:03:30,706 --> 01:03:35,277
This is a picture
your grandfather
took of me in paris.

529
01:03:35,279 --> 01:03:37,179
Wow.

530
01:03:37,181 --> 01:03:39,781
Your mother used to love
to look through these pictures.

531
01:03:39,783 --> 01:03:43,385
She'd always say she was
gonna visit all these places.

532
01:03:43,387 --> 01:03:45,287
Really?

533
01:03:45,289 --> 01:03:47,956
All of her favorite stories
were of me and your grandfather.

534
01:03:47,958 --> 01:03:51,026
She couldn't sleep at night
without a story.

535
01:03:53,930 --> 01:03:56,097
Why'd she leave?

536
01:03:56,099 --> 01:03:58,934
Well, your mother
was very ambitious.

537
01:03:58,936 --> 01:04:02,470
She had a long list
of things she wanted
to do in her life.

538
01:04:02,472 --> 01:04:04,806
Like what?

539
01:04:04,808 --> 01:04:08,510
Like ride something
bigger than a horse.

540
01:04:08,512 --> 01:04:11,179
Travel around the world,
write a book.

541
01:04:11,181 --> 01:04:13,381
After graduation,
she wanted to
go to college,

542
01:04:13,383 --> 01:04:15,884
and god bless her,
she got in.

543
01:04:15,886 --> 01:04:18,153
She wanted to
study abroad.

544
01:04:18,155 --> 01:04:20,121
What did she
wanna study?

545
01:04:20,123 --> 01:04:22,157
She didn't know.
She just wanted
to get outta here.

546
01:04:22,159 --> 01:04:24,259
Out of colorado.

547
01:04:24,261 --> 01:04:26,494
That was at the top
of her list, to get
as far away

548
01:04:26,496 --> 01:04:28,563
as she could from here.

549
01:04:31,667 --> 01:04:35,804
You know,
she never finished school.

550
01:04:35,806 --> 01:04:38,940
- She didn't?
- No.

551
01:04:38,942 --> 01:04:42,611
Because of me, she didn't
do half the things that
you just said.

552
01:04:42,613 --> 01:04:45,614
- It's not your fault.
- Then whose is it?

553
01:04:45,616 --> 01:04:47,682
Aldo.

554
01:04:57,493 --> 01:04:59,594
I'm just tired.

555
01:06:15,371 --> 01:06:17,105
Hey.

556
01:06:18,874 --> 01:06:20,575
Hi.

557
01:06:24,347 --> 01:06:27,182
Writing your book?

558
01:06:27,184 --> 01:06:31,019
More like thoughts
rather than a book.

559
01:06:32,922 --> 01:06:36,491
Whatcha thinkin' about?

560
01:06:36,493 --> 01:06:39,794
If I told you,
they wouldn't be thoughts,

561
01:06:39,796 --> 01:06:41,796
but something I said,

562
01:06:41,798 --> 01:06:43,932
which would make it
a quote,

563
01:06:43,934 --> 01:06:46,368
and I'm not
writing quotes, so...

564
01:06:46,370 --> 01:06:49,337
But you're writing it down.

565
01:06:51,307 --> 01:06:53,308
But I'm the only one
readin"em,

566
01:06:53,310 --> 01:06:55,543
so they still stay
my thoughts.

567
01:06:59,448 --> 01:07:02,350
You write about me?

568
01:07:06,155 --> 01:07:10,225
- Wouldn't you
like to know?
- I would.

569
01:07:16,432 --> 01:07:18,266
I would.

570
01:07:23,172 --> 01:07:25,440
Okay, but if I read
you something,

571
01:07:25,442 --> 01:07:27,609
you gotta promise
not to laugh.

572
01:07:27,611 --> 01:07:30,278
- What if it's funny?
- No, you gotta promise.

573
01:07:30,280 --> 01:07:32,680
- No laughing.
- Scout's honor.

574
01:07:32,682 --> 01:07:35,283
Isn't that only valid
if you're actually a scout?

575
01:07:35,285 --> 01:07:38,520
I was for,
like, 15 days,
but who's counting?

576
01:07:40,589 --> 01:07:42,323
Okay.

577
01:07:49,031 --> 01:07:52,000
"In jersey,

578
01:07:52,002 --> 01:07:54,402
I'd never find this."

579
01:07:59,675 --> 01:08:04,245
See, I first wrote this
because...

580
01:08:04,247 --> 01:08:07,148
I so badly wanted
to take back how
I treated you.

581
01:08:13,689 --> 01:08:15,924
"Be nice to her.

582
01:08:15,926 --> 01:08:18,660
"Because to wake up
and see her

583
01:08:18,662 --> 01:08:21,062
there's nothing better."

584
01:08:30,940 --> 01:08:34,709
I'm sorry.
I shouldn't
have done that.

585
01:08:37,113 --> 01:08:38,980
Wait.

586
01:08:54,263 --> 01:08:57,098
Well, can I hear
some more?

587
01:08:57,100 --> 01:08:59,000
No.

588
01:09:00,970 --> 01:09:03,972
But can i
see you again?

589
01:09:03,974 --> 01:09:06,407
No.

590
01:09:20,823 --> 01:09:22,590
You're glowing.

591
01:09:24,593 --> 01:09:28,997
- I am?
- She's a nice girl.

592
01:09:30,533 --> 01:09:33,868
- Who?
- Madalyn.

593
01:09:36,272 --> 01:09:38,840
- Yeah, she's pretty cool.
- Just cool?

594
01:09:38,842 --> 01:09:41,342
Come on, grandma, what--

595
01:09:41,344 --> 01:09:45,980
ooh, grandma.
I like it.

596
01:09:47,750 --> 01:09:49,817
Yeah. Me, too.

597
01:09:54,290 --> 01:09:55,823
What's the rush?

598
01:09:58,127 --> 01:10:00,929
Gotta get some sleep.
Madalyn wants to go
horseback riding tomorrow.

599
01:10:00,931 --> 01:10:03,598
Do you know how
to ride a horse?

600
01:10:03,600 --> 01:10:05,767
No, but how hard
can it be?

601
01:10:05,769 --> 01:10:08,436
- Hey, aldo?
- Yeah?

602
01:10:08,438 --> 01:10:11,005
You okay now?

603
01:10:14,276 --> 01:10:18,213
No, but for once,
I know I will be.

604
01:10:38,334 --> 01:10:40,201
First time really?

605
01:10:40,203 --> 01:10:42,670
There's more to this city boy
than you think.

606
01:10:51,747 --> 01:10:54,315
Yeah, I'm beginning
to see that.

607
01:11:01,857 --> 01:11:03,758
Hey, you hungry?

608
01:11:03,760 --> 01:11:05,927
- Yeah.
- Let's go.

609
01:11:15,838 --> 01:11:18,106
This is actually
pretty good.

610
01:11:18,108 --> 01:11:24,646
Good to know, 'cause
it's about the only
thing I make good.

611
01:11:24,648 --> 01:11:28,549
I'll have you know I'm actually
a wolfgang puck in the making.

612
01:11:31,020 --> 01:11:32,987
He's a famous chef.

613
01:11:32,989 --> 01:11:36,858
Yeah, I knew that.

614
01:11:36,860 --> 01:11:39,494
Yeah.

615
01:11:42,164 --> 01:11:44,866
What's the city like?

616
01:11:46,435 --> 01:11:48,670
You've never left
this place?

617
01:11:48,672 --> 01:11:51,572
No.

618
01:11:51,574 --> 01:11:55,443
Everyone who lives here
is practically born
and raised here,

619
01:11:55,445 --> 01:11:57,912
just like their parents.

620
01:12:02,251 --> 01:12:04,819
Well, it's loud,
for one.

621
01:12:04,821 --> 01:12:08,589
Unlike this place.

622
01:12:08,591 --> 01:12:10,758
And it's definitely
not like this

623
01:12:10,760 --> 01:12:13,995
when you're sittin' behind
a red light in traffic.

624
01:12:15,364 --> 01:12:19,434
- Where are you from?
- Trenton.

625
01:12:19,436 --> 01:12:22,570
It's in new joisey.

626
01:12:22,572 --> 01:12:24,572
I know a trenton.

627
01:12:24,574 --> 01:12:25,773
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

628
01:12:25,775 --> 01:12:29,177
I'm sure there's
no relation.

629
01:12:32,414 --> 01:12:35,917
My dad lives
in california.

630
01:12:45,327 --> 01:12:47,995
Your dad lives
in california?

631
01:12:47,997 --> 01:12:50,198
Mm-hmm.

632
01:12:50,200 --> 01:12:54,302
Him and my mom
got a divorce
about three years ago.

633
01:12:54,304 --> 01:12:57,138
I mean, they fought
all the time.

634
01:13:06,081 --> 01:13:08,783
You never told me that.

635
01:13:08,785 --> 01:13:11,586
Aldo, it's not a big deal.

636
01:13:11,588 --> 01:13:14,655
That's everyone's story.

637
01:13:14,657 --> 01:13:17,258
Who cares? You just...

638
01:13:17,260 --> 01:13:21,329
Have to deal with it
the best way you can.

639
01:13:23,265 --> 01:13:26,501
There are no victims
in life.

640
01:13:26,503 --> 01:13:29,337
Life happens to us all.

641
01:13:32,941 --> 01:13:35,610
When your father left,

642
01:13:35,612 --> 01:13:37,845
how did it feel?

643
01:13:37,847 --> 01:13:40,415
Good.

644
01:13:40,417 --> 01:13:42,917
[Chuckles]

645
01:13:42,919 --> 01:13:45,153
seriously.

646
01:13:56,899 --> 01:13:59,133
I hated him so much.

647
01:14:00,469 --> 01:14:04,472
I hated him so much
for taking the easy way out.

648
01:14:06,008 --> 01:14:08,476
And I hated my mom
for letting him.

649
01:14:16,084 --> 01:14:18,753
You asked me
why I was here.

650
01:14:21,190 --> 01:14:24,492
I'm here because
I was in a car
accident with my mom.

651
01:14:26,495 --> 01:14:29,330
I wish god had
taken me, but he didn't.

652
01:14:35,971 --> 01:14:38,339
It gets better.

653
01:14:38,341 --> 01:14:42,643
- When?
- I don't know,
but it does.

654
01:14:47,149 --> 01:14:49,884
Come on.
Day's not over yet.

655
01:15:13,909 --> 01:15:17,011
This is beautiful.

656
01:15:18,447 --> 01:15:20,481
Nothin' like this
in the city?

657
01:15:22,618 --> 01:15:25,386
One can only wish.

658
01:15:29,324 --> 01:15:31,759
I used to come here a lot.

659
01:15:31,761 --> 01:15:34,462
Not anymore.

660
01:15:34,464 --> 01:15:37,798
Not for a long time now.

661
01:15:37,800 --> 01:15:39,634
Why?

662
01:15:41,103 --> 01:15:44,672
This is my dad's
favorite spot.

663
01:15:47,142 --> 01:15:50,811
I used to come here
after he left.

664
01:15:50,813 --> 01:15:54,715
It sucks losing someone
that you can't replace.

665
01:15:56,685 --> 01:15:59,754
You still have
the memory, though.

666
01:16:01,757 --> 01:16:03,858
And when I think about it,

667
01:16:05,627 --> 01:16:07,995
I feel it.

668
01:16:10,966 --> 01:16:14,468
And it's as though
the memory was
never lost at all.

669
01:16:27,082 --> 01:16:29,684
So it's okay to be happy.

670
01:16:41,663 --> 01:16:43,965
You'll never forget her.

671
01:16:46,101 --> 01:16:48,869
It's like breathing.

672
01:17:04,453 --> 01:17:06,354
Hey.

673
01:17:06,356 --> 01:17:08,823
Hi. Always writing, huh?

674
01:17:10,325 --> 01:17:13,394
Got a lot to say.

675
01:17:13,396 --> 01:17:16,631
I, uh,

676
01:17:16,633 --> 01:17:18,966
I wanted to give you this.

677
01:17:18,968 --> 01:17:20,635
What is it?

678
01:17:20,637 --> 01:17:24,505
It's a letter that
I never mailed.

679
01:17:27,576 --> 01:17:30,645
- It's to mom.
- Open it.

680
01:17:35,417 --> 01:17:37,918
What does it say?

681
01:17:37,920 --> 01:17:40,154
[Laughs]

682
01:17:40,156 --> 01:17:43,024
I wish my memory
were that good.

683
01:17:44,893 --> 01:17:47,395
Why didn't
you send it?

684
01:17:47,397 --> 01:17:49,397
Oh, I don't know.

685
01:17:49,399 --> 01:17:52,533
So many reasons.
I'm sure they were
all stupid.

686
01:18:00,242 --> 01:18:02,677
- You read it.
- Okay.

687
01:18:05,080 --> 01:18:06,981
Okay.

688
01:18:18,727 --> 01:18:21,062
"Dear emilia,

689
01:18:21,064 --> 01:18:25,266
"I've spent the past months
looking around this empty house,

690
01:18:25,268 --> 01:18:29,537
"and staring back at me
is nothing but an empty feeling.

691
01:18:32,507 --> 01:18:36,077
"And now I fear
there's no changing that.

692
01:18:36,079 --> 01:18:38,779
"How did we get here?

693
01:18:38,781 --> 01:18:41,816
"I ask myself that
so many times.

694
01:18:41,818 --> 01:18:44,819
"I love you, honey,

695
01:18:45,887 --> 01:18:50,191
"and I was afraid for you.

696
01:18:53,562 --> 01:18:57,398
"The world is not
what pictures
paint it to be.

697
01:18:57,400 --> 01:19:01,702
"I never wanted you to
miss out on everything
you were made for.

698
01:19:05,907 --> 01:19:10,444
"But I realize now
what you were made for

699
01:19:10,446 --> 01:19:12,847
"is more than what
was around you.

700
01:19:17,052 --> 01:19:19,620
"I'm sorry, emilia.

701
01:19:22,290 --> 01:19:24,225
"If I could have
another chance

702
01:19:24,227 --> 01:19:27,094
"to tell you
what I should've said

703
01:19:27,096 --> 01:19:30,297
"when you asked to leave,
I would say,

704
01:19:30,299 --> 01:19:35,803
"'don't miss out on
everything that's out there.

705
01:19:35,805 --> 01:19:38,906
"'Until you spread your wings,

706
01:19:38,908 --> 01:19:43,644
you'll have no idea...'"

707
01:19:43,646 --> 01:19:46,480
[Laughs]

708
01:19:46,482 --> 01:19:48,816
"how far you can fly.'

709
01:19:54,756 --> 01:19:56,791
"Love, mom."

710
01:20:06,802 --> 01:20:09,603
She would've
loved that.

711
01:20:09,605 --> 01:20:11,739
You should have
sent it.

712
01:20:11,741 --> 01:20:15,376
Oh, there's a lot of
things I should've done.

713
01:20:20,115 --> 01:20:22,550
If you could,

714
01:20:22,552 --> 01:20:25,719
would you take
everything and change it?

715
01:20:25,721 --> 01:20:27,988
Of course I would.

716
01:20:27,990 --> 01:20:31,058
Then that's
all that matters.

717
01:20:33,895 --> 01:20:36,497
I guess we both
have to learn that.

718
01:20:38,567 --> 01:20:43,003
And just live
a little more,
bit by bit each day.

719
01:20:44,773 --> 01:20:49,310
I would do anything
to bring her back,

720
01:20:49,312 --> 01:20:51,979
but I can't.

721
01:20:54,883 --> 01:20:57,351
And neither can you.

722
01:21:00,655 --> 01:21:02,990
When did you get so wise?

723
01:21:02,992 --> 01:21:05,526
I don't know.

724
01:21:07,128 --> 01:21:10,030
I guess I'm just
ready to start
living again.

725
01:21:12,334 --> 01:21:14,602
But I want you
to live with me.

726
01:21:14,604 --> 01:21:17,771
- Me?
- Yes.

727
01:21:17,773 --> 01:21:20,841
Okay?

728
01:21:20,843 --> 01:21:23,077
Okay.

729
01:21:23,079 --> 01:21:26,046
- Okay?
- Okay. Okay.

730
01:21:49,905 --> 01:21:55,576
?

731
01:22:14,663 --> 01:22:19,800
?

732
01:22:29,210 --> 01:22:36,617
?

733
01:22:54,069 --> 01:23:01,075
?

734
01:23:15,290 --> 01:23:21,628
?

735
01:23:42,250 --> 01:23:48,288
?

736
01:23:48,290 --> 01:23:50,824
Give it gas,
give it gas.

737
01:23:50,826 --> 01:23:52,960
Keep pushing.
I got this.

738
01:23:52,962 --> 01:23:54,962
Go, go, go!

739
01:23:54,964 --> 01:23:57,064
Yes!

740
01:23:58,633 --> 01:24:01,802
Wait!

741
01:24:15,884 --> 01:24:18,318
- Where are we going?
- You'll see.

742
01:24:44,913 --> 01:24:47,448
Wow.

743
01:24:54,589 --> 01:24:57,024
No way.

744
01:25:01,396 --> 01:25:03,597
- Is that you?
- Yeah.

745
01:25:03,599 --> 01:25:07,034
I was something
to marvel at, wasn't ' i?

746
01:25:08,903 --> 01:25:11,071
That was
back in the day.

747
01:25:11,073 --> 01:25:14,808
I used to dance
and be wild and free.

748
01:25:17,112 --> 01:25:19,980
That was a long time ago.

749
01:25:19,982 --> 01:25:24,218
Things have changed a bit.

750
01:25:30,825 --> 01:25:34,161
- Did you hear that?
- What?

751
01:25:34,163 --> 01:25:37,698
- The music.
- What music?

752
01:25:40,335 --> 01:25:42,302
Take my hand.

753
01:25:46,875 --> 01:25:50,611
- May I have
this dance?
- Yes.

