01:59:40,374 --> 01:59:42,741
No warning,
no phone call.

1012
01:59:42,743 --> 01:59:46,044
That makes him and you
more alike than you think.

1013
01:59:47,313 --> 01:59:50,115
You should talk to him.

1014
01:59:58,157 --> 02:00:01,960
I'm here for you,
whatever you decide.

1015
02:02:27,473 --> 02:02:30,875
You want anything to drink?

1016
02:02:30,877 --> 02:02:35,380
Yeah, I could use
something to drink. Thanks.

1017
02:02:39,885 --> 02:02:42,454
It's a little warm.

1018
02:02:42,456 --> 02:02:44,422
It's from earlier.

1019
02:02:45,658 --> 02:02:47,692
It's fine.

1020
02:02:47,694 --> 02:02:50,395
Thanks.

1021
02:03:01,474 --> 02:03:03,842
I didn't think
you'd come.

1022
02:03:03,844 --> 02:03:06,444
To think all I could say,
all I would say...

1023
02:03:06,446 --> 02:03:08,546
You know, I never knew.

1024
02:03:09,615 --> 02:03:12,083
Knew what?

1025
02:03:17,156 --> 02:03:19,457
About you.

1026
02:03:22,795 --> 02:03:25,897
Yeah. I, uh...

1027
02:03:27,633 --> 02:03:30,969
I dated your mom...

1028
02:03:30,971 --> 02:03:33,705
When she was a freshman
at perdue,

1029
02:03:33,707 --> 02:03:37,342
and I was a senior
in high school,

1030
02:03:37,344 --> 02:03:40,945
till one day,
she just up and left.

1031
02:03:43,382 --> 02:03:46,017
Now I know why.

1032
02:03:48,020 --> 02:03:50,221
Why now?

1033
02:03:57,062 --> 02:03:59,264
I don't know.

1034
02:04:05,504 --> 02:04:07,572
They called
over a year ago.

1035
02:04:09,308 --> 02:04:11,509
Left a voicemail.

1036
02:04:13,212 --> 02:04:15,947
By the time I got
the courage to call back,

1037
02:04:15,949 --> 02:04:18,049
months had already passed.

1038
02:04:20,953 --> 02:04:25,190
To find out
you have a son, overnight...

1039
02:04:27,793 --> 02:04:30,528
I can't tell you
how that felt.

1040
02:04:32,565 --> 02:04:35,266
Why didn't she tell me?

1041
02:04:36,869 --> 02:04:39,804
Did she think I wouldn't
be a good father?

1042
02:04:42,341 --> 02:04:46,878
I would've loved you
the best I could.

1043
02:04:46,880 --> 02:04:49,347
I deserve that.

1044
02:04:50,816 --> 02:04:54,853
That was just
taken away from me.

1045
02:05:04,296 --> 02:05:06,231
You have a family now?

1046
02:05:06,233 --> 02:05:10,869
Yeah.
Three girls.

1047
02:05:12,271 --> 02:05:15,840
Six, ten, and, uh... 14.

1048
02:05:18,878 --> 02:05:21,546
- No mom?
- No.

1049
02:05:21,548 --> 02:05:26,017
She left me and the girls
a short time after
emily was born.

1050
02:05:26,019 --> 02:05:28,786
I was never the best man
for her,

1051
02:05:28,788 --> 02:05:32,557
but she always seemed to
give me another try.

1052
02:05:32,559 --> 02:05:34,959
Emily.

1053
02:05:34,961 --> 02:05:39,130
Yeah, emily's the youngest,
and sasha's the middle,

1054
02:05:39,132 --> 02:05:42,166
and then, savannah...

1055
02:05:42,168 --> 02:05:44,435
God, I tell you,

1056
02:05:44,437 --> 02:05:48,006
you look exactly how
I thought you'd look.

1057
02:05:49,141 --> 02:05:51,276
What did you expect?

1058
02:05:51,278 --> 02:05:55,547
You look like her.
Emilia.

1059
02:06:03,455 --> 02:06:05,189
I'm sorry.

1060
02:06:06,292 --> 02:06:08,092
Sorry.

1061
02:06:14,967 --> 02:06:17,769
Ya know...

1062
02:06:17,771 --> 02:06:22,006
I really could've
used a father after
what happened.

1063
02:06:27,279 --> 02:06:30,114
You know, I just...

1064
02:06:30,116 --> 02:06:33,952
I wondered if I'd
make things worse.

1065
02:06:36,488 --> 02:06:39,524
Hell, you'd just
lost your mother.

1066
02:06:39,526 --> 02:06:43,127
Would you have even
wanted me around?

1067
02:06:43,129 --> 02:06:46,097
Person you didn't
even know?

1068
02:06:48,367 --> 02:06:51,269
But when you find out
you have a son,

1069
02:06:51,271 --> 02:06:54,973
or just a child
in general,

1070
02:06:54,975 --> 02:06:58,009
it's, like,
nothing is the same.

1071
02:06:58,011 --> 02:07:00,378
I started
to search for you,

1072
02:07:00,380 --> 02:07:02,647
but you had already
turned 18; c.P.S.
Had closed your file,

1073
02:07:02,649 --> 02:07:05,216
wouldn't tell me
a damn thing.

1074
02:07:05,218 --> 02:07:08,486
But I felt like
if I never tried,
I would never know.

1075
02:07:08,488 --> 02:07:11,189
- I always say that.
- Say what?

1076
02:07:11,191 --> 02:07:13,791
If you never try,
you'll never know.

1077
02:07:28,440 --> 02:07:30,541
I promise you...

1078
02:07:34,113 --> 02:07:37,615
If I'd have known
she was pregnant...

1079
02:07:42,054 --> 02:07:45,189
I'd have been
a good father to you.

1080
02:07:50,062 --> 02:07:52,897
Yeah, you seem like it.

1081
02:07:56,135 --> 02:07:58,603
Thank you.

1082
02:08:09,615 --> 02:08:11,683
It's just, my life...

1083
02:08:11,685 --> 02:08:14,819
It's been so difficult
lately.

1084
02:08:14,821 --> 02:08:16,888
Every time I take
a couple of steps forward,

1085
02:08:16,890 --> 02:08:19,557
it's like something
sends me four steps back.

1086
02:08:19,559 --> 02:08:22,293
Then there's this girl,
and I didn't wanna hurt her,

1087
02:08:22,295 --> 02:08:24,929
and I just...
I really messed things up.

1088
02:08:24,931 --> 02:08:27,598
Now I don't even...

1089
02:08:27,600 --> 02:08:30,468
- Sorry, never mind.
- No, no. Tell me.

1090
02:08:30,470 --> 02:08:32,336
Tell me.

1091
02:08:35,774 --> 02:08:38,676
Well, I love her.

1092
02:08:38,678 --> 02:08:40,478
I think.

1093
02:08:40,480 --> 02:08:42,814
You never been in love?

1094
02:08:42,816 --> 02:08:45,249
I don't know.
How do you know?

1095
02:08:47,519 --> 02:08:49,420
Hoo!

1096
